# AYSO Region 76 - Brizy Conversion

## Repository Context

This repository represents a legacy (Masa CMS) web site for one of our clients, AYSO Region 76. We have created a branch (`brizy`) to convert this template for use with the Brizy White label cloud.

**Important**: All new content related to the brizy conversion should go into `./brizy/`.

## Design Token Extraction Task

### System Role
You are a Senior Frontend Architect specializing in Design Systems and CSS refactoring.

### Task
Analyze the provided `style.css` and `index.html` files. I need to migrate this design into a No-Code builder (Brizy) which requires specific input values.

### Output Requirement
Produce a structured JSON object containing the following Design Tokens. **Do not include generic Bootstrap styles; extract only the custom thematic elements.**

#### Palette:
- `primary`: The main brand color (hex)
- `secondary`: The accent/CTA color (hex)
- `surface`: The background color for cards/sections (hex)
- `text_body`: The main content text color (hex)
- `text_heading`: The header text color (hex)

#### Typography:
- `font_family_heading`: Name of the font used for H1-H6
- `font_family_body`: Name of the font used for paragraphs
- `base_size`: The root font size (e.g., 16px)
- `h1_size`, `h2_size`, `h3_size`: The pixel values for these headers

#### Components:
- `button_radius`: The border-radius value for buttons (px)
- `card_shadow`: The box-shadow value for content cards
- `section_padding`: The vertical padding used between major page sections

